ndary education is typically required for BC PNP sector positions, and candidates can earn extra points for Canadian education, particularly in British Columbia. Additionally, points are awarded for educational assessments from qualified institutions and Industry Training Authority British Columbia (ITAB) certification.<\/p>\n\n<table id=\"tablepress-22\" class=\"tablepress tablepress-id-22 tablepress-responsive\">\n<thead>\n<tr class=\"row-1 odd\">\n\t<th class=\"column-1\">Education Level<\/th><th class=\"column-2\">Points<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody class=\"row-hover\">\n<tr class=\"row-2 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Master\u2019s or Doctorate\/PhD<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">27<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-3 odd\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Post-Graduate Certificate or Diploma*<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">22<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-4 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Bachelor\u2019s Degree<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">15<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-5 odd\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Post-secondary Diploma\/Certificate (Trades)**<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">15<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-6 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Associate Degree<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">5<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-7 odd\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Post-secondary Diploma\/Certificate (Non-trades)<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">5<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-8 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Secondary School (High School) or Less<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">0<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-9 odd\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\"><\/td><td class=\"column-2\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-10 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Additional points:<br \/>\n(NOTE: you can only receive additional points for ONE of the<br \/>\nfollowing)<\/td><td class=\"column-2\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-11 odd\">\n\t<td class=\"column-1\">Post-secondary education completed in B.C.<\/td><td class=\"column-2\">8<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr class=\"row-12 even\">\n\t<td class=\"column-